description: a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2; for n > 2, a(n) is the smallest positive number that has not yet appeared that, given the list of primes that form the factors of all previous terms a(1)..a(n-1), is a multiple of the prime in that list which is a factor of the fewest previous terms. If two or more such primes exist the smallest is chosen.
